column2: Partly cloudy.  Winds about 10 mph. Macrophytes were interfering with an accurate Secchi Disc reading. We moved about 150 east of desired location to do the measurement. This is at the edge of the dense part of the plant growth.
Sunny day. Light winds.  Found open water just a short distance from sampling location
Sunny and warm.  Lake water looks very green
Sunny- lake is green- 10 mph winds so wavey
Mild wind- sunny- and very green water
some wind- relatively few aquatic plants at surface
Sunny day- calm wind- little cloud cover
